<PageLayout
  title="Community Guidelines"
  eyebrow="House rules"
  heading="Community Guidelines"
  intro="Short, sweet, and meant to keep Duncit a place worth being."
  accent="tertiary"
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522202176988-66273c2fd55f?w=1600&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop"
>
  <h2>1. Be kind</h2>
  <p>Treat people the way you'd want to be treated on your worst Monday. Hate, harassment, or threats of any kind earn an instant exit.</p>

  <h2>2. Be real</h2>
  <p>Use a real photo and a name people can call you. Catfishing, impersonation, and bots are removed on sight.</p>

  <h2>3. Keep it safe</h2>
  <p>No nudity, no doxxing, no sharing private info without consent. If a chat feels off, hit the report button — a human will respond.</p>

  <h2>4. Don't sell, don't spam</h2>
  <p>Duncit isn't a marketplace or an MLM funnel. Promo links and recruitment messages get filtered.</p>

  <h2>5. Respect privacy</h2>
  <p>What's shared in chat stays in chat. Screenshots without permission are not the move.</p>

  <h2>6. Use the tools</h2>
  <p>Block, mute, and report exist for a reason. Use them freely — and we'll back you up.</p>

  <h2>If something goes wrong</h2>
  <p>Reach out to <a href="mailto:safety@duncit.com">safety@duncit.com</a> or use the in-app report flow. Our Trust & Safety team reviews every report, every time.</p>
</PageLayout>
